
# 2026-02-12 03:25:36.705785
+The sensor-playground project is a Raspberry Pi sensor dashboard (tkinter, 800x480 touchscreen) that currently displays live data from 18 sensors (temperature, humidity, pressure, light, UV, air quality, motion, etc.) plus a USB webcam with LLM-powered scene description. The owner wants to transform it into a conversational assistant dashboard where an LLM interprets the sensor data, responds to questions, and provides insights. The current UX is a static tkinter GUI with category tabs on an 800x480 touchscreen. The VPS at dr.eamer.dev already runs APIs and has Claude/xAI/OpenAI provider access. Questions: (1) Should it stay tkinter or move to a web UI served locally? (2) How should the LLM be integrated - local on Pi 3B+ or via VPS API? (3) What UX patterns work for a split dashboard+chat on 800x480? (4) What's the best architecture for a sensor-aware conversational assistant? (5) How should sensor context be fed to the LLM? Give concrete architecture recommendations.

